" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533249\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 14, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vyz1665702990742.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vyz1665702990742.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vyz1665702990742.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vyz1665702990742\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Use Third-Party DLLs in a Custom Print Dialog\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can extend the custom print dialog box to use a third-party DLL to change Microsoft Windows printer settings.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__topic_d65162e1_d65163e1_d65164e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__p_d65165e1_d65166e1_d65167e1\">To use external DLLs:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28271e1_d28272e1_d28273e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a non-modal form as described in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lwh1665702990671.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lwh1665702990671.html\" title=\"You can create your own print dialog box that includes an operation to handle printing.\">Creating a Custom Print Dialog</a>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28274e1_d28275e1_d28276e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Add the DLL to the [USER_3GL] section of your assignment file.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28277e1_d28278e1_d28279e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Register a signature for the DLL in the Signature Editor.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28280e1_d28281e1_d28282e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Obtain declarations for the DLL functions from the DLL's documentation.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28283e1_d28284e1_d28285e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Make a corresponding Uniface signature for the DLL based on the DLL function declarations.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28286e1_d28287e1_d28288e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Access DLL functions using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> statements in the print dialog.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28289e1_d28290e1_d28291e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Draw a drop-down list of available print job models, using a ValRep in the format of <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintJobModel</var>=<var class=\"keyword varname\">DescriptiveText</var>.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> A print job model is still required by Uniface, even if printer settings are handled by third-party printing software.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28292e1_d28293e1_d28294e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Draw a drop-down list to select <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintMode</var>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28295e1_d28296e1_d28297e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span> instruction, set <code class=\"ph codeph\">USE_SYSTEM_SETTINGS=TRUE</code>. This prevents the print job model overriding the Microsoft Windows printer settings made by the third-party DLL.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vyz1665702990742__li_d28298e1_d28299e1_d28300e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Return the user’s choices to the parent form. Process the information to provide <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintJobModel</var>, <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintMode</var>, and <var class=\"keyword varname\">Settings</var> information to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span> statement.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533249\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533249\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Use Third-Party DLLs in a Custom Print Dialog Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Use Third-Party DLLs in a Custom Print Dialog You can extend the custom print dialog box to use a third-party DLL to change Microsoft Windows printer settings. To use external DLLs: Create a non-modal form as described in Creating a Custom Print Dialog . Add the DLL to the [USER_3GL] section of your assignment file. Register a signature for the DLL in the Signature Editor. Obtain declarations for the DLL functions from the DLL's documentation. Make a corresponding Uniface signature for the DLL based on the DLL function declarations. Access DLL functions using activate statements in the print dialog. Draw a drop-down list of available print job models, using a ValRep in the format of PrintJobModel = DescriptiveText . Note: A print job model is still required by Uniface, even if printer settings are handled by third-party printing software. Draw a drop-down list to select PrintMode . In the print instruction, set USE_SYSTEM_SETTINGS=TRUE . This prevents the print job model overriding the Microsoft Windows printer settings made by the third-party DLL. Return the user’s choices to the parent form. Process the information to provide PrintJobModel , PrintMode , and Settings information to the print statement. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}